WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.720 --> 00:00:05.680
These are the true events
of November. 1965--

2
00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:08.280
The la Drang Valley of Vietnam--

3
00:00:08.360 --> 00:00:10.920
a place our country
does not remember...

4
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.400
in a war
it does not understand.

5
00:00:14.800 --> 00:00:17.000
This story's a testament
to the young Americans...

6
00:00:17.080 --> 00:00:19.000
who died in the Valley of Death...

7
00:00:19.040 --> 00:00:21.520
and a tribute to the young men
of the Peoples Army of Vietnam...

8
00:00:21.560 --> 00:00:24.480
who died by our hand
in that place.

9
00:00:26.800 --> 00:00:29.720
To tell this story.
l must start at the beginning.

10
00:00:31.560 --> 00:00:33.440
But where does it begin?

11
00:00:35.880 --> 00:00:39.360
Maybe in June of 1954.
when French Group Mobile 100...

12
00:00:39.440 --> 00:00:42.320
moved into the same
Central Highlands of Vietnam...

13
00:00:42.360 --> 00:00:44.840
where we would go 11 years later.

14
00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:21.800
LoS PiRaTaS 2002
***by Kurgan***

15
00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:45.320
Maybe the story
begins in America...

16
00:03:45.400 --> 00:03:49.240
when the army first realized a new
kind of war was coming its way.

17
00:03:49.320 --> 00:03:51.880
The White House anticipates
a buildup and wants a victory...

18
00:03:51.960 --> 00:03:53.880
over cavemen in black pajamas.

19
00:03:53.960 --> 00:03:56.480
We wouldn't be there if they hadn't
already beaten the French Army.

20
00:03:56.600 --> 00:03:59.560
The French Army?
What's that?

21
00:03:59.600 --> 00:04:02.840
The problem in Vietnam is terrain--
jungles. mountains. rivers.

22
00:04:02.880 --> 00:04:04.320
Maneuver's a nightmare.

23
00:04:04.400 --> 00:04:07.720
We have a plan to use helicopters--
leap in and out of battle.

24
00:04:07.800 --> 00:04:09.800
They want you
to run the test on the idea.

25
00:04:09.880 --> 00:04:12.600
It'll take a hell
of a combat leader.

26
00:04:12.680 --> 00:04:15.160
I know a young light colonel
named Hal Moore.

27
00:04:15.240 --> 00:04:17.160
He led a combat company in Korea.

28
00:04:17.240 --> 00:04:19.880
After that. he volunteered
to test experimental parachutes.

29
00:04:19.960 --> 00:04:23.600
Experimental parachutes?
Sounds like just the guy.

30
00:04:23.680 --> 00:04:28.120
The other side of the mountain
was all that he could see

31
00:04:28.200 --> 00:04:32.160
Was all that he could see
Was all that he could see

32
00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:37.320
The other side of the mountain
was all that he could see

33
00:04:37.400 --> 00:04:41.080
The bear went over the mountain
The bear went over the mountain

34
00:04:41.160 --> 00:04:42.600
The bear went over the mountain

35
00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:46.240
How about we go back to ''Bingo''?
What do you say? ''Bingo.''

36
00:04:47.520 --> 00:04:49.520
B-l-N-G-O

37
00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:51.240
B-l-N-G-O

38
00:04:51.320 --> 00:04:53.320
B-l-N-G-O

39
00:04:53.360 --> 00:04:55.760
And Bingo was his name-o

40
00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:16.720
Tom. how much you know
about our new colonel?

41
00:05:16.800 --> 00:05:18.360
He was in Korea...

42
00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:20.840
has a master's in international
relations from Harvard.

43
00:05:20.880 --> 00:05:24.320
Harvard? He's not one of those
academic pussies. is he?

44
00:05:24.400 --> 00:05:25.880
Hal Moore?

45
00:05:25.920 --> 00:05:28.080
Want me to get one of those?

46
00:06:18.720 --> 00:06:22.120
Come on. Too Tall.
Gimme your best shot!

47
00:06:23.800 --> 00:06:26.680
Did you see that. sports fans?
Did you see that?

48
00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:29.240
Snakeshit drives that one
to the moon. baby!

49
00:06:29.320 --> 00:06:31.800
Hit the cutoff man!
Hit the cutoff man!

50
00:06:31.880 --> 00:06:34.080
And he's coming around!

51
00:06:34.160 --> 00:06:37.280
- Here he comes!
- No. he's not.

52
00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:43.760
You're out!
You're out!

53
00:06:43.840 --> 00:06:47.080
Horseshit! No wonder you can't fly.
You can't see.

54
00:06:49.520 --> 00:06:51.440
I believe you're out.

55
00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:01.360
- You're a pilot?
- Too Tall. sir.

56
00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:04.360
- Yeah. I can see that.
- You call. we haul.

57
00:07:07.120 --> 00:07:09.040
- Can I speak to you. Crandall?
- Yes. sir.

58
00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:11.240
- Out.
- Safe.

59
00:07:11.320 --> 00:07:13.360
- Out.
- Safe.

60
00:07:15.200 --> 00:07:17.160
- Can I buy you a drink?
- Sure.

61
00:07:17.240 --> 00:07:18.680
Thanks.

62
00:07:18.760 --> 00:07:22.000
So. your men
call you ''Snakeshit.''

63
00:07:22.040 --> 00:07:25.760
That's an affectionate appellation
of my comrades-in-arms. sir...

64
00:07:25.840 --> 00:07:27.840
'cause I fly
lower than snake shit.

65
00:07:27.920 --> 00:07:31.920
Well. I got a problem. Snakeshit.
and I think you're the solution.

66
00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:34.480
I've been called a lot of things.
Colonel. never a solution.

67
00:07:34.600 --> 00:07:37.120
You know what air cavalry
really means?

68
00:07:37.200 --> 00:07:41.520
You fly into hostile territory.
outnumbered. 10.000 miles from home.

69
00:07:41.600 --> 00:07:43.800
Sometimes the battleground's
no bigger than a football field.

70
00:07:43.840 --> 00:07:48.160
And if the choppers stop comin'.
we all get slaughtered.

71
00:07:48.240 --> 00:07:51.160
Now. I figure chopper pilots
won't fly into hell for strangers...

72
00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:53.800
so... I'm Hal Moore.

73
00:07:53.840 --> 00:07:55.960
I know. sir.
Why us?

74
00:07:57.160 --> 00:08:01.240
Well. you guys look like shit.
but your equipment is immaculate.

75
00:08:02.200 --> 00:08:05.280
Yesterday was Sunday. You didn't
have to be training. but you were.

76
00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:07.160
You got pilots
like that Too Tall character.

77
00:08:07.240 --> 00:08:10.280
He's way outside the limits
of army regs.

78
00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:12.800
They wanna fly with you
for some reason.

79
00:08:12.840 --> 00:08:14.800
I guess it's 'cause
they think you're the best.

80
00:08:14.840 --> 00:08:17.400
It's 'cause I only recruit
the dumb ones. sir.

81
00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:23.520
I don't suppose
I have a choice in all this.

82
00:08:23.600 --> 00:08:26.280
You sure don't.

83
00:08:27.320 --> 00:08:29.000
Wouldn't miss it for the world.

84
00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.600
To the Air Cav.

85
00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:40.960
Good mornin'. Sergeant-Major.

86
00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:44.000
How do you know what kind
of goddamn day it is?

87
00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:55.160
Group! Atten-hut!

88
00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:21.600
At ease. gentlemen.

89
00:09:23.320 --> 00:09:25.400
Welcome to the new cavalry.

90
00:09:26.920 --> 00:09:28.840
We will ride into battle.

91
00:09:30.160 --> 00:09:33.120
And this... will be our horse.

92
00:09:57.960 --> 00:10:01.440
You don't have to catch it.
You don't have to feed it.

93
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:04.600
But I can assure you...

94
00:10:05.680 --> 00:10:09.960
that neither the new technology
nor your status as officers...

95
00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:12.320
will keep you above the danger.

96
00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:17.600
Sergeant-Major Plumley and I
come from the paratroopers...

97
00:10:17.680 --> 00:10:21.240
where the officer is always
the first one out of the plane.

98
00:10:22.320 --> 00:10:24.240
Because to follow
your instincts...

99
00:10:24.320 --> 00:10:27.320
and to inspire your men
by your example...

100
00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:33.240
you have to be with them
where the metal meets the meat.

101
00:10:34.120 --> 00:10:36.840
Sergeant-Major Plumley
made all four combat jumps...

102
00:10:36.920 --> 00:10:39.440
in the 82nd Airborne
during World War II.

103
00:10:39.560 --> 00:10:41.640
Sicily. Salerno. Normandy...

104
00:10:41.720 --> 00:10:44.800
and Holland.
plus one more in Korea.

105
00:10:46.680 --> 00:10:49.800
He answers to me
and to me alone.

106
00:10:49.840 --> 00:10:52.800
Now. I hope you gentlemen
like training...

107
00:10:52.840 --> 00:10:55.160
'cause me
and the sergeant-major--

108
00:10:56.400 --> 00:10:58.320
we love it.

109
00:11:00.320 --> 00:11:03.960
Three strikes
and you're not out!

110
00:11:04.040 --> 00:11:07.000
There is always
one more thing you can do.

111
00:11:18.160 --> 00:11:19.600
Here we go. boys.

112
00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:21.920
Move! Move! Go! Now!

113
00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.120
- Two.
- Let's go!

114
00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:26.120
Three.

115
00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:27.600
We're outta here!

116
00:11:28.680 --> 00:11:30.680
- Pretty good. huh?
- Pretty good.

117
00:11:32.840 --> 00:11:34.920
There's only one thing wrong.

118
00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:39.280
Be sharp! We will be the best
platoon in this battalion!

119
00:11:39.320 --> 00:11:41.800
Be ready in there!
Let's go! Let's go!

120
00:11:41.840 --> 00:11:44.440
All right!
Your officer's dead!

121
00:11:44.560 --> 00:11:46.480
- What do you do? What do you do?
- First--

122
00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:49.520
All right. he hesitated.
He's dead. What do you do?

123
00:11:49.600 --> 00:11:51.760
- Get off the chopper!
- Get off of the chopper.

124
00:12:00.680 --> 00:12:02.240
Hold off the third one.

125
00:12:03.320 --> 00:12:04.840
Come on in.

126
00:12:04.920 --> 00:12:08.440
Savage. you learn the job
of the man above you...

127
00:12:08.480 --> 00:12:10.840
and you teach your job
to the man below you in rank.

128
00:12:10.920 --> 00:12:12.840
That goes for every man
in this outfit.

129
00:12:12.920 --> 00:12:14.480
- Understood?
- Yes. sir!

130
00:12:14.600 --> 00:12:17.240
We'll be landing
under fire. gentlemen.

131
00:12:20.480 --> 00:12:21.920
Men will die.

132
00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:30.920
Have you said your prayers?

133
00:12:33.200 --> 00:12:34.880
Come on.
I'll say them with you.

134
00:12:36.040 --> 00:12:38.040
- Fall in.
- Gimme that bear.

135
00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:43.640
All right.
Ready. Set.

136
00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:47.120
In the name of the Father.
the Son and the Holy Ghost.

137
00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:50.360
Hail Mary. full of grace.
the Lord is with thee.

138
00:12:50.400 --> 00:12:52.320
Blessed art thou amongst women...

139
00:12:52.400 --> 00:12:54.000
and blessed is
the fruit of thy womb Jesus.

140
00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:56.840
Holy Mary. Mother of God.
pray for us sinners--

141
00:12:56.920 --> 00:12:58.880
Cecile. I don't hear you
praying. honey.

142
00:13:00.360 --> 00:13:04.000
I don't wanna be Catholic.
I wanna be a ''Nethodist'' like Mommy.

143
00:13:04.080 --> 00:13:06.000
You do?

144
00:13:06.040 --> 00:13:08.200
And why is that. honey?

145
00:13:08.240 --> 00:13:10.320
So I can pray whatever I want.

146
00:13:11.280 --> 00:13:12.480
That's a sin.

147
00:13:12.600 --> 00:13:14.560
No. that's not a sin.

148
00:13:14.600 --> 00:13:17.800
God just made you hardheaded.
It's not a sin.

149
00:13:17.880 --> 00:13:21.360
I'll tell you what.
You wanna--

150
00:13:21.440 --> 00:13:23.960
You wanna pray and thank God
for our family?

151
00:13:25.040 --> 00:13:28.320
- Yes. sir.
- That's good. Let's do it.

152
00:13:28.360 --> 00:13:31.920
Hail Mary. full of grace.
the Lord is with thee.

153
00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:34.080
Blessed art thou among women...

154
00:13:34.160 --> 00:13:36.320
and blessed is
the fruit of thy womb. Jesus.

155
00:13:41.920 --> 00:13:44.400
I can hear you laughing.
you know. even in here.

156
00:13:44.480 --> 00:13:47.280
I'm not laughing.
I'm marveling.

157
00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:49.640
Marveling? At what?

158
00:13:49.720 --> 00:13:52.040
That you can find stubbornness
in your children...

159
00:13:52.080 --> 00:13:54.680
and think it comes
from anybody but you.

160
00:13:54.720 --> 00:13:56.160
- Yeah?
- Mm-hmm.

161
00:13:59.560 --> 00:14:02.000
I'll give you something
to marvel at.

162
00:14:05.360 --> 00:14:06.840
He's a wild man.

163
00:14:25.040 --> 00:14:27.720
- When I pray--
- Mm-hmm.

164
00:14:27.800 --> 00:14:29.200
whatever I want--

165
00:14:30.560 --> 00:14:32.440
I thank God for you.

166
00:14:46.720 --> 00:14:48.640
Beautiful morning.
Sergeant-Major.

167
00:14:48.720 --> 00:14:51.120
What are you.
a fuckin' weatherman now?

168
00:14:54.200 --> 00:14:57.560
Look what I found
for the new baseball player.

169
00:14:57.600 --> 00:15:00.000
- Sent us another bunch of officers.
- Uh-huh.

170
00:15:00.040 --> 00:15:02.560
Real green.
Gotta train 'em up.

171
00:15:02.600 --> 00:15:04.920
Makes me think
I'm starting a new unit.

172
00:15:05.000 --> 00:15:07.080
They sent new rifles too.
The M-16.

173
00:15:07.160 --> 00:15:09.080
That's supposed to be
a pretty good weapon.

174
00:15:09.160 --> 00:15:11.080
Lots of plastic.

175
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:15.680
Feels like a BB gun to me.
Believe I'll stick with my pistol.

176
00:15:15.760 --> 00:15:18.760
You think we're gonna get close
enough to the enemy to use that?

177
00:15:18.840 --> 00:15:20.320
What do you think. sir?

178
00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:23.560
A leader must remain
cool and calm.

179
00:15:23.600 --> 00:15:27.520
And second. he must learn
to ignore explosions...

180
00:15:27.600 --> 00:15:30.360
the heat and dust.
the screams of the wounded.

181
00:15:31.400 --> 00:15:35.000
This is normal on a battlefield.
Normal!

182
00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:51.840
Fortran. you need to get a company
over to reinforce the left flank.

183
00:15:51.920 --> 00:15:55.520
- Where is that coming from?
- That's our advisors in Vietnam.

184
00:15:55.600 --> 00:15:58.560
The new radio's picking up
atmospheric bounce.

185
00:16:17.040 --> 00:16:19.040
When Crazy Horse was a baby...

186
00:16:23.120 --> 00:16:26.680
he nursed from the breast
of every woman in the tribe.

187
00:16:29.080 --> 00:16:31.240
The Sioux raised
their children that way.

188
00:16:32.280 --> 00:16:33.720
Every warrior...

189
00:16:34.800 --> 00:16:36.800
called every woman
in the tribe ''mother.''

190
00:16:37.880 --> 00:16:40.240
Every older warrior.
they called him ''grandfather.''

191
00:16:40.320 --> 00:16:43.560
Now. the point here is that
they fought as a family.

192
00:16:45.200 --> 00:16:47.160
Take care of your men.

193
00:16:48.200 --> 00:16:51.200
Teach them to take care
of each other.

194
00:16:51.240 --> 00:16:53.200
'Cause when this starts...

195
00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.160
each other
is all we're gonna have.

196
00:17:03.080 --> 00:17:06.200
- Did you tune that in?
- Yes. sir.

197
00:17:06.280 --> 00:17:08.560
Well. that's fine.
You're my radio operator.

198
00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:12.640
You'll be fine.
You'll work it out.

199
00:17:19.440 --> 00:17:22.440
Any of you sons of bitches
calls me Grandpa...

200
00:17:25.080 --> 00:17:26.960
I'll kill ya.

201
00:17:49.720 --> 00:17:52.800
Godboldt. take your boots off.

202
00:17:52.880 --> 00:17:54.600
Go on.

203
00:17:56.240 --> 00:18:00.320
Everybody. take your boots off.
Everybody.

204
00:18:00.400 --> 00:18:02.640
Socks too.

205
00:18:15.400 --> 00:18:17.920
I want you to draw
fresh socks from supply.

206
00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:20.640
Keep your feet
dusted with powder.

207
00:18:24.320 --> 00:18:27.760
Everybody check each other's feet
like Godboldt and me.

208
00:18:29.600 --> 00:18:31.560
Now. that young man's a leader.

209
00:18:31.600 --> 00:18:33.160
Yes. sir.

210
00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:36.480
That other fella--
that big. strong one there--

211
00:18:36.560 --> 00:18:38.480
he wants to win medals.

212
00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:43.680
Why were you in the back?

213
00:18:43.720 --> 00:18:45.840
Goddamn it.
why were you in the back?

214
00:18:46.920 --> 00:18:48.880
He's eager.

215
00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:54.760
Ladies. I'm really. really glad
you're here today.

216
00:18:55.760 --> 00:19:00.040
Some of you are new to the army
and all of us are new to this post.

217
00:19:00.120 --> 00:19:03.640
I thought we'd pool our resources
and cover questions we have.

218
00:19:03.720 --> 00:19:06.920
So. why don't we start
with item number one-- food.

219
00:19:08.800 --> 00:19:10.360
Where's the best place to shop?

220
00:19:12.760 --> 00:19:14.720
Well. I tried Big Star.
and it's okay.

221
00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:17.880
But I keep thinking my water's gonna
break right in the checkout aisle.

222
00:19:21.120 --> 00:19:24.960
That takes care of food shopping.
So. item number two-- laundry.

223
00:19:25.040 --> 00:19:26.480
The base washing machines
don't work.

224
00:19:26.560 --> 00:19:28.840
They're full of sand
from the swamp missions.

225
00:19:28.920 --> 00:19:30.560
I'll take care of that.

226
00:19:30.640 --> 00:19:33.680
- I've already complained.
- We'll just go to the general.

227
00:19:35.360 --> 00:19:38.040
In the meantime.
the Laundromat in town's okay...

228
00:19:38.120 --> 00:19:40.640
but they won't let you wash your
colored things in their machines.

229
00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:43.560
- At a public Laundromat?
- Didn't make sense to me either.

230
00:19:43.640 --> 00:19:45.560
I'm telling you. they have
a sign right in the window...

231
00:19:45.640 --> 00:19:46.960
says ''Whites Only.''

232
00:19:50.320 --> 00:19:53.880
- What?
- They mean white people only.

233
00:19:55.720 --> 00:19:57.160
That's awful.

234
00:19:58.040 --> 00:20:01.160
Your husband is wearing the uniform
of a country that allows a place...

235
00:20:02.440 --> 00:20:06.800
to say his laundry's not
good enough. when he could die for--

236
00:20:11.920 --> 00:20:14.040
- I'm sorry. I just--
- That's all right. honey.

237
00:20:14.120 --> 00:20:18.000
I know what my husband's fighting
for. and that's why I can smile.

238
00:20:18.040 --> 00:20:20.600
My husband will never
ask for respect...

239
00:20:21.360 --> 00:20:23.760
and he'll give respect to no man
who hasn't earned it.

240
00:20:23.840 --> 00:20:26.040
The rest of his family
is the same way.

241
00:20:26.080 --> 00:20:29.200
Anybody who doesn't respect that
can keep his washing machine...

242
00:20:29.280 --> 00:20:31.360
'cause my baby's clothes
are gonna be clean anyway.

243
00:20:34.440 --> 00:20:37.280
Well. I guess that takes care
of item number two.

244
00:20:40.360 --> 00:20:42.160
Are you all right?

245
00:20:42.240 --> 00:20:46.280
I think-- I think
my water just broke.

246
00:20:46.360 --> 00:20:48.840
We're all calm.
We're all calm.

247
00:20:49.880 --> 00:20:52.200
A car! A car!

248
00:21:25.760 --> 00:21:27.720
- Colonel.
- At ease. At ease.

249
00:21:27.760 --> 00:21:30.000
I heard one of my new lieutenants
just became a father.

250
00:21:30.080 --> 00:21:32.000
- I came to say congratulations.
- Thank you. sir.

251
00:21:32.840 --> 00:21:34.760
So. I didn't wanna disturb you.

252
00:21:34.840 --> 00:21:37.960
No. it's fine.
It's all right. Please.

253
00:21:38.040 --> 00:21:39.960
Well. how's your wife?

254
00:21:40.040 --> 00:21:42.640
She's okay. She's okay.
She's sleeping.

255
00:21:43.720 --> 00:21:46.120
So is my daughter.
I just...

256
00:21:46.200 --> 00:21:48.760
wanted to be here for a while
before I held her.

257
00:21:48.840 --> 00:21:51.000
Well. tag her already?

258
00:21:51.080 --> 00:21:53.600
- What's that say?
- Camille. Sorry about this. sir.

259
00:21:53.680 --> 00:21:56.320
Don't take that off. Leave that
where it is. That's an order.

260
00:21:58.880 --> 00:22:01.680
- Colonel. may I ask you a question?
- Sure.

261
00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:07.800
What do you think about
being a soldier and a father?

262
00:22:09.120 --> 00:22:11.200
I hope that being good
at the one...

263
00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:13.280
makes me better at the other.

264
00:22:15.960 --> 00:22:18.240
Why? What about you?

265
00:22:18.320 --> 00:22:21.080
I don't know. sir.

266
00:22:21.160 --> 00:22:23.080
Between college and here...

267
00:22:24.440 --> 00:22:26.560
Barbara and I
spent a year in Africa.

268
00:22:28.360 --> 00:22:31.720
We helped build a school
for orphans.

269
00:22:33.360 --> 00:22:36.000
They were orphans because
the warlord across the border...

270
00:22:36.080 --> 00:22:38.040
didn't like their tribe.

271
00:22:41.240 --> 00:22:44.880
I know God has a plan for me.

272
00:22:46.080 --> 00:22:48.720
I just hope it's to help
protect orphans...

273
00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:52.080
not make any.

274
00:22:54.800 --> 00:22:57.840
Well. why don't we ask him?

275
00:22:57.920 --> 00:23:00.000
Come on.
Let's go ask him.

276
00:23:05.240 --> 00:23:08.200
Our Father in Heaven.
before we go into battle...

277
00:23:09.200 --> 00:23:12.480
every soldier among us will
approach you each in his own way.

278
00:23:13.720 --> 00:23:15.640
Our enemies too...

279
00:23:15.720 --> 00:23:17.280
according to
their own understanding...

280
00:23:17.360 --> 00:23:20.120
will ask for protection
and for victory.

281
00:23:20.200 --> 00:23:23.360
And so. we bow before
your infinite wisdom.

282
00:23:23.400 --> 00:23:25.800
We offer our prayers
as best we can.

283
00:23:26.720 --> 00:23:30.240
I pray you watch over the young men.
like Jack Geoghegan...

284
00:23:30.320 --> 00:23:33.680
that I lead into battle.

285
00:23:33.760 --> 00:23:36.200
You use me as your instrument
in this awful hell of war...

286
00:23:36.280 --> 00:23:38.040
to watch over them.

287
00:23:39.680 --> 00:23:41.960
Especially if they're
men like this one beside me...

288
00:23:42.040 --> 00:23:44.760
deserving of a future
in your blessing and good will.

289
00:23:47.080 --> 00:23:49.160
- Amen.
- Amen.

290
00:23:51.440 --> 00:23:54.360
Yes. and one more thing.
dear Lord...

291
00:23:54.440 --> 00:23:55.880
about our enemies--

292
00:23:58.160 --> 00:23:59.600
ignore their heathen prayers...

293
00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:01.720
and help us blow those
little bastards straight to hell.

294
00:24:02.560 --> 00:24:04.000
Amen again.

295
00:24:05.800 --> 00:24:07.200
Amen.

296
00:24:07.280 --> 00:24:08.720
Thank you.

297
00:24:12.560 --> 00:24:15.280
There's one about the kid with the
apple tree. or the flying horse...

298
00:24:15.360 --> 00:24:19.280
or the fairy tales
with the deer and stuff in 'em.

299
00:24:19.320 --> 00:24:22.000
Daddy. what is a war?

300
00:24:27.160 --> 00:24:29.120
A war is a--

301
00:24:29.160 --> 00:24:31.120
Well. it's--

302
00:24:34.320 --> 00:24:38.640
It's something that
shouldn't happen. but it does.

303
00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:42.920
It's when...

304
00:24:42.960 --> 00:24:47.160
some people--
in another country or any country--

305
00:24:48.080 --> 00:24:51.760
try to take the lives
of other people.

306
00:24:51.840 --> 00:24:54.480
And then soldiers
like your daddy have to--

307
00:24:54.600 --> 00:24:57.120
It's my job to go over there
and stop them.

308
00:24:58.480 --> 00:25:02.640
Are they gonna try to
take your life away. Daddy?

309
00:25:06.800 --> 00:25:09.640
Well. yes. they're gonna try.

310
00:25:09.720 --> 00:25:11.640
But I'm not gonna let 'em.

311
00:25:13.200 --> 00:25:14.120
Okay?

312
00:26:18.840 --> 00:26:20.280
Can't sleep?

313
00:26:25.880 --> 00:26:28.280
The men are so young and--

314
00:26:28.320 --> 00:26:31.000
Now they sent me a new crop
even greener.

315
00:26:32.200 --> 00:26:35.040
When I look at them. I...

316
00:26:35.120 --> 00:26:36.600
see our boys.

317
00:26:37.680 --> 00:26:40.640
Well. then you're
just the man to lead them.

318
00:26:44.160 --> 00:26:46.120
I guess.

319
00:26:58.280 --> 00:27:01.520
We intend to convince
the Communists...

320
00:27:02.720 --> 00:27:07.640
that we cannot be defeated
by force of arms.

321
00:27:08.680 --> 00:27:13.280
l have asked the commanding general.
General Westmoreland...

322
00:27:13.360 --> 00:27:18.240
what more he needs to meet
this mounting aggression.

323
00:27:19.280 --> 00:27:21.360
He has told me...

324
00:27:22.800 --> 00:27:25.560
and we will meet his needs.

325
00:27:27.440 --> 00:27:30.800
l have today ordered to Vietnam
the airmobile division...

326
00:27:30.880 --> 00:27:34.080
and certain other forces which
will raise our fighting strength...

327
00:27:34.120 --> 00:27:36.880
from 75.000 to...

328
00:27:36.960 --> 00:27:40.640
125.000 men almost immediately.

329
00:27:41.800 --> 00:27:44.200
Additional forces
will be needed later.

330
00:27:45.960 --> 00:27:47.960
Get out your best dresses.
ladies.

331
00:27:50.040 --> 00:27:52.000
They're gonna want to celebrate.

332
00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:08.120
Don't you ever be sad

333
00:28:08.160 --> 00:28:12.240
Lean on me
when the times are bad

334
00:28:15.160 --> 00:28:17.440
I didn't hear the president
mention a state of emergency.

335
00:28:17.560 --> 00:28:19.000
No. he didn't.

336
00:28:19.080 --> 00:28:23.080
Well. without that declaration
our enlistments won't be extended.

337
00:28:23.160 --> 00:28:25.840
I'm sorry. Hal.

338
00:28:25.920 --> 00:28:28.920
Forgive me. sir.
but let me get this straight.

339
00:28:29.000 --> 00:28:32.480
We form a division using techniques
never attempted in battle...

340
00:28:32.600 --> 00:28:36.840
against an enemy with 20 years of
combat experience on his ground...

341
00:28:36.920 --> 00:28:39.600
12.000 miles away
from our ground.

342
00:28:39.640 --> 00:28:42.440
And right before the army
sends us into the fight...

343
00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:45.840
they take away a third of my most
experienced men. including officers.

344
00:28:45.920 --> 00:28:49.000
I don't like it
any better than you do. Hal.

345
00:28:51.280 --> 00:28:53.720
You saw this coming. didn't you?

346
00:28:53.800 --> 00:28:57.720
Yes. That's why you gave me
that new crop of platoon leaders.

347
00:28:59.800 --> 00:29:01.760
Korea didn't teach 'em anything.

348
00:29:01.840 --> 00:29:04.280
- Politicians?
- Politicians.

349
00:29:09.840 --> 00:29:13.200
Hold me. hold me

350
00:29:13.280 --> 00:29:15.400
Never let me go

351
00:29:15.440 --> 00:29:20.040
Until you've told me
told me

352
00:29:20.120 --> 00:29:24.960
What l want to know
and then just hold me

353
00:29:25.040 --> 00:29:27.760
Hold me
Make me tell you

354
00:29:27.800 --> 00:29:31.960
I'm in love with you

355
00:29:36.720 --> 00:29:39.760
Thrill me. thrill me

356
00:29:41.120 --> 00:29:42.720
Thank you. sir.

357
00:29:42.800 --> 00:29:44.920
By the way. Hal.
since we're being deployed...

358
00:29:44.960 --> 00:29:46.440
they're renumbering the units.

359
00:29:46.560 --> 00:29:48.000
You're now
the commanding officer...

360
00:29:48.040 --> 00:29:50.960
of the 1st Battalion
of the 7th Cavalry.

361
00:29:53.760 --> 00:29:55.160
The 7th.

362
00:29:56.640 --> 00:29:58.600
The same regiment as Custer.

363
00:30:03.080 --> 00:30:04.320
Thank you. sir.

364
00:30:04.400 --> 00:30:07.600
Be sensible with your new love

365
00:30:09.120 --> 00:30:11.440
Don't be fooled thinking

366
00:30:11.520 --> 00:30:15.840
This is the last
you'll find

367
00:30:15.920 --> 00:30:18.800
But they never stood
in the dark

368
00:30:18.840 --> 00:30:22.000
With you. love

369
00:30:22.080 --> 00:30:25.040
When you take me
in your arms

370
00:30:25.120 --> 00:30:29.440
And drive me slowly
out of my mind

371
00:30:29.520 --> 00:30:32.280
Kiss me. kiss me

372
00:30:32.360 --> 00:30:34.760
And when you do
I'll know

373
00:32:12.160 --> 00:32:14.240
Look around you.

374
00:32:16.400 --> 00:32:19.080
In the 7th Cavalry...

375
00:32:19.160 --> 00:32:22.160
we got a captain
from the Ukraine.

376
00:32:23.240 --> 00:32:26.240
Another from Puerto Rico.

377
00:32:26.320 --> 00:32:28.680
We've got Japanese. Chinese...

378
00:32:28.760 --> 00:32:31.680
Blacks. Hispanics.
Cherokee Indians.

379
00:32:32.840 --> 00:32:35.960
Jews and gentiles.

380
00:32:36.040 --> 00:32:38.480
All Americans.

381
00:32:38.600 --> 00:32:41.600
Now. here in the States...

382
00:32:41.680 --> 00:32:44.840
some men in this unit...

383
00:32:44.920 --> 00:32:49.280
may experience discrimination
because of race or creed.

384
00:32:49.360 --> 00:32:51.280
But for you and me now...

385
00:32:52.920 --> 00:32:54.360
all that is gone.

386
00:32:55.400 --> 00:32:58.920
We're moving into the Valley
of the Shadow of Death...

387
00:33:00.760 --> 00:33:04.640
where you will watch
the back of the man next to you...

388
00:33:04.720 --> 00:33:06.880
as he will watch yours.

389
00:33:06.920 --> 00:33:09.320
And you won't care
what color he is...

390
00:33:09.360 --> 00:33:12.840
or by what name he calls God.

391
00:33:13.920 --> 00:33:15.880
They say we're leaving home.

392
00:33:18.600 --> 00:33:22.120
We're going to what home
was always supposed to be.

393
00:33:24.760 --> 00:33:27.760
So let us understand
the situation.

394
00:33:27.840 --> 00:33:30.760
We are going into battle...

395
00:33:30.840 --> 00:33:33.840
against a tough
and determined enemy.

396
00:33:38.800 --> 00:33:41.320
I can't promise you...

397
00:33:41.400 --> 00:33:44.640
that I will bring you
all home alive.

398
00:33:46.040 --> 00:33:47.680
But this I swear--

399
00:33:49.120 --> 00:33:52.440
before you and before
Almighty God--

400
00:33:52.560 --> 00:33:54.440
that when we go into battle...

401
00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:59.120
I will be the first
to set foot on the field...

402
00:34:00.600 --> 00:34:03.080
and I will be
the last to step off.

403
00:34:05.440 --> 00:34:08.920
And I will leave no one behind.

404
00:34:13.440 --> 00:34:15.400
Dead or alive...

405
00:34:17.280 --> 00:34:19.760
we will all come home together.

406
00:34:22.080 --> 00:34:24.600
So help me God.

407
00:37:50.760 --> 00:37:52.680
I love you.

408
00:40:50.680 --> 00:40:54.400
Hal. last night the enemy
hit our camp at Plaei Me.

409
00:40:54.480 --> 00:40:56.000
- How many casualties?
- None.

410
00:40:57.280 --> 00:40:59.200
The enemy forces withdrew
toward this mountain...

411
00:40:59.280 --> 00:41:00.920
near the Cambodian border.

412
00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:03.200
How many men do you have
battle-ready?

413
00:41:03.280 --> 00:41:06.080
- Sergeant Major?
- Three hundred ninety-five. sir.

414
00:41:06.160 --> 00:41:08.280
Exactly.

415
00:41:08.360 --> 00:41:09.840
What do you estimate
the enemy strength?

416
00:41:09.920 --> 00:41:12.240
We appraise their numbers
as manageable. Colonel.

417
00:41:13.880 --> 00:41:15.280
You have no idea.

418
00:41:16.280 --> 00:41:18.920
We have no idea.
Simple orders. Hal.

419
00:41:19.000 --> 00:41:21.320
Find the enemy and kill him.

420
00:41:24.280 --> 00:41:28.480
They attack us. no casualties.
They run and hide in the mountains.

421
00:41:29.160 --> 00:41:31.080
Naturally we chase them. of course.

422
00:41:32.560 --> 00:41:35.000
Smell like an ambush to you?

423
00:41:35.040 --> 00:41:38.960
They get close enough to kill us.
we'll be close enough to kill them.

424
00:41:43.120 --> 00:41:45.400
Round trip by chopper. 30 minutes.

425
00:41:45.520 --> 00:41:50.120
So the first 60 men on the ground
will be there a half an hour alone.

426
00:41:50.200 --> 00:41:51.680
Son of a bitch.

427
00:41:52.880 --> 00:41:56.400
I think maybe you ought to
get yourself that M-16.

428
00:41:56.480 --> 00:42:00.440
Time comes I need one. there'll be
plenty of'em lying on the ground.

429
00:42:05.560 --> 00:42:08.800
Well. let's go do
what we came here to do.

430
00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:11.280
Yes. sir.

431
00:42:24.480 --> 00:42:25.960
Garry Owen!

432
00:43:35.560 --> 00:43:37.960
It was a Sunday.

433
00:43:38.040 --> 00:43:40.880
November 14. 1965.

434
00:43:42.040 --> 00:43:45.160
Before that day.
the soldiers of North Vietnam...

435
00:43:45.240 --> 00:43:46.680
and those of America...

436
00:43:46.760 --> 00:43:49.640
never met each other
in a major battle.

437
00:44:18.160 --> 00:44:20.920
Two miles out.
Dropping to nap of the earth.

438
00:47:23.160 --> 00:47:26.320
First Platoon. let's move!

439
00:47:36.640 --> 00:47:40.600
This is Trojan Two. All units
maintain perimeter contact. Over.

440
00:47:44.720 --> 00:47:46.680
It's a scout!
Let's take him prisoner!

441
00:47:47.760 --> 00:47:49.120
Hey! Lieutenant!

442
00:47:54.320 --> 00:47:56.600
There he goes! Come on!

443
00:48:01.280 --> 00:48:02.840
Come on!

444
00:48:02.920 --> 00:48:05.760
Captain. I want you to
keep in contact with all patrols.

445
00:48:08.160 --> 00:48:10.800
Hey. I got something here.
I got a boy! here.

446
00:48:10.880 --> 00:48:12.160
Boy. hell.

447
00:48:12.240 --> 00:48:13.680
That ain't no boy.

448
00:48:18.680 --> 00:48:21.400
- He say he a deserter.
- Bullshit. he's a lookout.

449
00:48:21.520 --> 00:48:23.440
Ask him where his friends are.

450
00:48:30.080 --> 00:48:32.000
He say this is base camp
of whole division.

451
00:48:32.880 --> 00:48:34.760
- Four thousand men.
- Where?

452
00:48:40.560 --> 00:48:42.280
That mountain.

453
00:48:50.440 --> 00:48:52.000
Same army destroyed French.

454
00:48:52.080 --> 00:48:55.960
And he say they want kill American
very badly.

455
00:48:56.040 --> 00:48:58.080
Just not been able to find any yet.

456
00:48:58.160 --> 00:49:01.600
Captain Metsker. tell all patrols
to hold their positions.

457
00:49:10.280 --> 00:49:12.280
You. take the radio!

458
00:49:14.200 --> 00:49:17.240
- Where are they?
- Sir. we gotta get that guy!

459
00:49:23.640 --> 00:49:25.400
Call in all the patrols!

460
00:49:25.440 --> 00:49:28.760
We have to engage the enemy
as far away from the LZ as possible!

461
00:49:32.600 --> 00:49:34.480
Net Call. Net Call.
this is Trojan-Two.

462
00:49:34.600 --> 00:49:36.640
Grab the wounded!
Break contact!

463
00:49:37.680 --> 00:49:40.280
Fall back!
Get to high ground!

464
00:49:40.360 --> 00:49:43.120
Cover fire!
Get to high ground!

465
00:49:43.200 --> 00:49:44.600
Come on!

466
00:49:54.800 --> 00:49:57.840
Come on! Get up here!
Bring the wounded up to the middle!

467
00:49:57.920 --> 00:49:59.640
Move it. move it!

468
00:49:59.720 --> 00:50:02.000
Cover fire! Cover fire!

469
00:50:05.240 --> 00:50:07.840
Everybody down! Down!

470
00:50:10.840 --> 00:50:13.920
Check your ammo!
Everybody check ammo!

471
00:50:21.280 --> 00:50:23.200
Come on!
I'll get us out of here!

472
00:50:24.280 --> 00:50:26.760
Grab the wounded!
We'll make a run

473
00:50:26.840 --> 00:50:28.920
- Sarge!
- We gotta get out of here!

474
00:50:30.560 --> 00:50:33.840
Stay down! Don't anybody move!

475
00:50:33.920 --> 00:50:35.600
Bungum. stay down!

476
00:50:47.800 --> 00:50:49.320
You're gonna be okay.

477
00:50:52.560 --> 00:50:53.960
Stay down.

478
00:50:55.040 --> 00:50:56.560
Form a perimeter!

479
00:50:56.640 --> 00:50:59.920
Conserve your ammo and stay down!

480
00:51:02.080 --> 00:51:04.480
What's happening with those patrols?

481
00:51:04.600 --> 00:51:08.440
I'm trying to reach them. sir!
This is Trojan-Two! Come in! Over!

482
00:51:08.560 --> 00:51:12.160
Hey! Hey! Calm down!

483
00:51:12.240 --> 00:51:15.600
Understand the situation
and communicate clearly!

484
00:51:19.840 --> 00:51:23.400
Pull the chain on all the firepower
you can get on that mountain!

485
00:51:23.520 --> 00:51:26.160
Alert Crandall!
We have a hot LZ!!

486
00:51:26.240 --> 00:51:28.800
Agent Serpent-Six.
this is Trojan-Two.

487
00:51:28.880 --> 00:51:31.720
You're coming into a hot LZ.
We are taking fire.

488
00:51:31.800 --> 00:51:33.720
Repeat.
We are taking fire.

489
00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:36.240
No shit.

490
00:51:37.440 --> 00:51:39.960
This is Too Tall
goin'down and dirty.

491
00:51:44.880 --> 00:51:47.440
Roger that!
Trojan-Two. out!

492
00:51:47.560 --> 00:51:50.160
Herrick's platoon
is cut off and under attack.

493
00:51:50.240 --> 00:51:51.680
Bravo Company's holding.

494
00:51:52.760 --> 00:51:54.680
They're gonna try and flank us.

495
00:52:03.080 --> 00:52:05.120
On the ground now! Move!

496
00:52:06.760 --> 00:52:09.120
- Watch him!
- We gotta go.

497
00:52:09.200 --> 00:52:10.640
We're outta here.

498
00:52:10.680 --> 00:52:13.400
They're coming at us
from the back now! Move!

499
00:52:19.440 --> 00:52:20.880
Savage.

500
00:52:23.840 --> 00:52:26.240
All right. all right.
I got you.

501
00:52:27.560 --> 00:52:28.640
Sir?

502
00:52:29.760 --> 00:52:32.680
Don't let them
get the signal codes.

503
00:52:33.800 --> 00:52:35.520
Roger that. sir.

504
00:52:40.760 --> 00:52:43.960
I'm glad I could die
for my country.

505
00:52:55.280 --> 00:52:56.640
Doc.

506
00:53:13.640 --> 00:53:15.600
Bungum.

507
00:53:16.640 --> 00:53:18.080
Sarge?

508
00:53:23.800 --> 00:53:25.240
Tell my wife...

509
00:53:26.640 --> 00:53:28.040
I love her.

510
00:53:30.640 --> 00:53:32.080
This is Savage.

511
00:53:32.120 --> 00:53:36.760
I need artillery to these
coordinates: niner-3-3-0-1

512
00:53:39.680 --> 00:53:42.600
Ernie! Ernie. help!
We got more coming!

513
00:53:42.680 --> 00:53:45.240
We are cut off.
Copy? We are cut off.

514
00:53:47.800 --> 00:53:50.040
- Fire!
- Fire!

515
00:53:50.120 --> 00:53:52.720
- Fire!
- Fire!

516
00:53:53.720 --> 00:53:55.240
They're getting closer!

517
00:53:57.440 --> 00:53:59.680
They're getting closer!
A hundred more. sir!

518
00:54:07.760 --> 00:54:10.720
They're right on top of us. sir!
Bring it in close!

519
00:55:14.320 --> 00:55:18.280
It's a hot LZ! We'll be jumping!
We will not touch down.

520
00:55:31.680 --> 00:55:33.600
They're trying
to break right through us!

521
00:55:33.680 --> 00:55:37.800
I want you to reinforce
Alpha Company there! Now! Move!

522
00:55:37.880 --> 00:55:40.000
Follow me!
Charlie Company. up on the ridge!

523
00:55:40.080 --> 00:55:44.000
Doc. the wounded are over
by that termite mound! Go!

524
00:55:44.080 --> 00:55:46.840
Sir. if you don't find some cover.
you're gonna go down!

525
00:55:46.920 --> 00:55:49.400
If you go down. we all go down!
Come on!

526
00:56:05.200 --> 00:56:06.360
Cobain!

527
00:56:06.400 --> 00:56:09.520
I want the M-60 right here!

528
00:56:16.320 --> 00:56:17.760
Radio!

529
00:56:20.600 --> 00:56:23.040
Sir. it's Captain Edwards
on the ridge. sir!

530
00:56:24.080 --> 00:56:26.760
- Bob!
- Colonel. these guys are regulars!

531
00:56:26.840 --> 00:56:30.760
Heavily armed!
AK-47s and pouches of grenades!

532
00:56:30.840 --> 00:56:33.320
Heavy machine guns
and shoulder-fired rockets!

533
00:56:51.680 --> 00:56:53.360
Captain Nadal!

534
00:56:53.400 --> 00:56:56.320
That creek bed is vital.
Vital!

535
00:56:56.400 --> 00:56:59.320
They'll be coming right at you!
Do not let them flank!

536
00:56:59.400 --> 00:57:01.600
l repeat. do not let them flank!

537
00:57:02.160 --> 00:57:04.080
Secure the creek bed!

538
00:57:21.080 --> 00:57:24.000
Tom. I want you to keep trying
to raise those Medevac boys.

539
00:57:36.880 --> 00:57:38.920
I'm all right.

540
00:57:39.000 --> 00:57:40.920
Charlie. come here.

541
00:57:41.000 --> 00:57:44.600
Get me all the air support you
can get me on that mountain! Now!

542
00:57:44.680 --> 00:57:46.760
Requesting immediate
close air support!

543
00:57:46.840 --> 00:57:48.720
I need you to burn 'em out...

544
00:57:48.760 --> 00:57:53.160
on hilltop Alpha.
shift to Alpha Bravo!

545
00:57:53.240 --> 00:57:57.400
Coordinates: Golf-4-5-0-9!

546
00:58:12.400 --> 00:58:15.800
- Get me something higher up!
- Shifting to hilltop Bravo!

547
00:58:15.880 --> 00:58:19.200
Golf-4-5-7-2!

548
00:58:20.560 --> 00:58:24.240
I say again. 4-5-7-2!

549
00:58:36.240 --> 00:58:39.080
Medevac Command of the 7th Cavalry.
are you inbound?

550
00:58:39.160 --> 00:58:41.080
Looks pretty hot down there.

551
00:58:41.160 --> 00:58:44.680
Yeah. You can make it. though.
Watch our approach. follow us in.

552
00:58:44.760 --> 00:58:48.160
Copy that. 7th Cav.
We will follow your approach.

553
00:59:05.880 --> 00:59:09.320
I want you to get over there
and reinforce Charlie Company there!

554
00:59:11.560 --> 00:59:14.400
Medevac. abort! Abort!
This is a hot LZ!

555
00:59:14.480 --> 00:59:18.640
You see that? My Medevac guys are
buggin'out and leaving the wounded!

556
00:59:22.080 --> 00:59:23.240
We're going down!

557
00:59:33.240 --> 00:59:36.320
- Snake. get out of here!
- Bring me the wounded!

558
00:59:36.400 --> 00:59:37.960
Wounded! Get the wounded!

559
00:59:38.040 --> 00:59:39.840
Come on! Come on!

560
00:59:45.080 --> 00:59:46.800
Okay. here!

561
00:59:46.880 --> 00:59:49.800
They're still trying to flank us!
Stretch out along the line!

562
00:59:54.320 --> 00:59:55.760
Radio!

563
00:59:59.160 --> 01:00:02.960
Trojan-Six! We are in heavy contact!
In danger of being overrun!

564
01:00:03.040 --> 01:00:06.360
lf they get into that LZ.
we've all had it. Can you hold?

565
01:00:06.400 --> 01:00:08.960
We're spread thin. sir.
but we'll give 'em hell!

566
01:00:16.600 --> 01:00:19.560
Crandall. this is Trojan-Six.
It's too hot down here.

567
01:00:19.600 --> 01:00:22.560
- I'm closing the LZ.
- You copy that. Too Tall?

568
01:00:22.600 --> 01:00:24.640
Copy that. Snake.

569
01:00:24.720 --> 01:00:27.680
All 7th Cav air units.:
LZ X-Ray is closed.

570
01:00:27.760 --> 01:00:30.880
I don't like it. First time out.
a whole battalion massacred?

571
01:00:30.960 --> 01:00:33.120
You think this is a massacre?

572
01:00:33.200 --> 01:00:36.480
Losing draftees is a bad week.
Losing a colonel is a massacre.

573
01:00:36.600 --> 01:00:38.000
Moore is still fighting.

574
01:00:38.080 --> 01:00:40.120
He's under strength
against more men than he can count.

575
01:00:40.200 --> 01:00:42.880
- He's got a whole platoon lost.
- They're not lost.

576
01:00:42.920 --> 01:00:45.040
They're only cut off
and surrounded.

577
01:00:48.360 --> 01:00:49.960
Then they're lost.

578
01:00:50.040 --> 01:00:52.440
- Sergeant Major!
- Sir!

579
01:00:54.400 --> 01:00:57.880
We need to carve out
an emergency LZ right over there.

580
01:00:57.960 --> 01:00:59.960
- Sir!
- Blow the trees down!

581
01:01:09.440 --> 01:01:11.400
Fire in the hole!

582
01:01:17.320 --> 01:01:19.400
Colonel. this is Snakeshit
and Too Tall.

583
01:01:19.520 --> 01:01:21.360
We're comin' in
with two loads of ammo.

584
01:01:21.400 --> 01:01:23.400
Crandall. we've blown a new LZ.

585
01:01:23.560 --> 01:01:25.960
When you come in.
come in from the east. Out.

586
01:01:30.280 --> 01:01:32.400
Colonel. it's Brigade Headquarters.
They want you out.

587
01:01:32.440 --> 01:01:36.000
- Well. we can't get out. damn it!
- Not all of us. Just you.

588
01:01:36.080 --> 01:01:38.960
Saigon wants to debrief you.

589
01:01:39.040 --> 01:01:41.440
- That doesn't make any sense.
- Say again.

590
01:01:41.560 --> 01:01:43.920
Will you repeat that order?

591
01:01:49.840 --> 01:01:52.080
Too Tall. follow the colonel
to the new LZ.

592
01:01:52.120 --> 01:01:54.080
I see him. Snake.

593
01:01:58.120 --> 01:02:00.640
He's right here!
Let's go! Move!

594
01:02:03.120 --> 01:02:04.800
Let's move! Move!

595
01:02:05.800 --> 01:02:07.600
Oh. shit.

596
01:02:07.640 --> 01:02:10.960
- Come on! We'll give you a hand!
- We're moving on board!

597
01:02:11.040 --> 01:02:14.120
All right. get that ammo off
and get the wounded on!

598
01:02:14.200 --> 01:02:16.760
Bring 'em on!
Get 'em on. boys!

599
01:02:23.360 --> 01:02:25.040
No. we're overloaded!

600
01:02:25.120 --> 01:02:26.880
- Leave him!
- I'll get out! It's Ray!

601
01:02:26.960 --> 01:02:29.440
He's hurt worse than me!

602
01:02:30.440 --> 01:02:33.280
You hang on!
I'll see you back there. Ray!

603
01:02:58.560 --> 01:03:00.880
You. me and Ouellette
are all we have in reserve.

604
01:03:00.920 --> 01:03:03.520
Yeah. but it's
slacking up a little.

605
01:03:03.600 --> 01:03:07.160
No. they're just regrouping
for another assault.

606
01:03:07.240 --> 01:03:09.320
Distribute that ammo.

607
01:03:09.400 --> 01:03:13.440
Ouellette. tell Crandall he's got
time to get one more flight in here.

608
01:03:13.560 --> 01:03:14.480
Yes. sir.

609
01:03:18.200 --> 01:03:21.120
Doc. you give this water
to the wounded.

610
01:03:23.240 --> 01:03:26.200
Running out of water.
Must be terrible for 'em.

611
01:03:26.920 --> 01:03:29.360
Those guys are cut off out there.

612
01:03:35.040 --> 01:03:37.160
Running low on ammo. Sarge!

613
01:03:37.240 --> 01:03:40.080
Pick your target.
One shot. one kill.

614
01:03:40.120 --> 01:03:42.840
- Roger that. Sarge.
- How we doin'. Doc?

615
01:03:42.920 --> 01:03:44.920
Ernie. we're out of water.

616
01:03:46.400 --> 01:03:48.240
That's the last of it.

617
01:04:02.960 --> 01:04:04.880
My face is on fire! Help!

618
01:04:04.960 --> 01:04:07.400
Foster. hold still!
Hold still!

619
01:04:07.440 --> 01:04:09.240
I'll cut your face!
Hold still!

620
01:04:23.600 --> 01:04:25.760
Doc. Doc. it's Foster!

621
01:04:25.840 --> 01:04:27.080
Okay.

622
01:04:29.040 --> 01:04:31.560
Does anybody have
any more bandages?

623
01:04:48.120 --> 01:04:50.120
Ernie. you hit too?
You hit?

624
01:04:50.200 --> 01:04:51.600
No. no. I'm okay.

625
01:04:51.640 --> 01:04:53.920
Our guys are gonna
come for us. aren't they?

626
01:04:56.480 --> 01:04:57.760
Yeah.

627
01:04:57.840 --> 01:04:59.400
When?

628
01:05:01.440 --> 01:05:03.120
Plug his wound.

629
01:05:05.680 --> 01:05:08.640
That's the main LZ.
but it's closed.

630
01:05:18.960 --> 01:05:21.240
Go! Move!

631
01:05:23.680 --> 01:05:27.440
Go. Parker! Get up in there!
This is too Tall. I'm clear..

632
01:05:27.480 --> 01:05:29.800
Crandall's clear..

633
01:05:35.000 --> 01:05:36.400
Colonel!

634
01:05:36.480 --> 01:05:40.200
Go over and reinforce that company!
On that ridge there! Look!

635
01:05:40.240 --> 01:05:42.840
Yes. sir!
Okay! Keep your head down!

636
01:05:45.360 --> 01:05:47.400
To the top of the ridge!
Move it!

637
01:05:47.480 --> 01:05:49.520
Come on. let's move!
Move!

638
01:05:52.680 --> 01:05:54.080
Run! Come on!

639
01:06:00.880 --> 01:06:05.080
Captain Nadal. we've got to break
through to that cutoff platoon!

640
01:06:06.160 --> 01:06:08.880
We got an American platoon
out there.

641
01:06:08.960 --> 01:06:11.920
An Air Cav platoon cut off
out there!

642
01:06:12.000 --> 01:06:13.480
Air Cav!

643
01:06:14.440 --> 01:06:15.720
Garry Owen!

644
01:06:33.680 --> 01:06:35.680
He said. "Really? Me too."
I said. "I know.

645
01:06:35.720 --> 01:06:38.680
Your mama asked me
to give you $600."

646
01:06:41.160 --> 01:06:42.720
Good luck to you.

647
01:06:47.560 --> 01:06:49.680
Hey. you got enough room
for one more?

648
01:06:50.760 --> 01:06:53.720
If you're crazy enough. get in.
Yes. sir.

649
01:07:10.400 --> 01:07:13.000
Hey. what are those lights down there?

650
01:07:13.840 --> 01:07:15.960
Enemy soldiers.

651
01:07:16.040 --> 01:07:18.000
They use candles on the trail.

652
01:07:19.040 --> 01:07:21.440
They're moving into position to attack.

653
01:07:24.840 --> 01:07:26.800
Here we go!

654
01:07:48.760 --> 01:07:53.200
Unload that shit!
Let's go. let's go. let's go. let's go!

655
01:07:58.240 --> 01:08:01.360
You and your boys have done
a hell of a job today. Snake.

656
01:08:02.080 --> 01:08:06.720
It's the last flight for the night.
but you need us. you call us.

657
01:08:10.400 --> 01:08:13.360
Who in the hell are you?
I'm a reporter. sir.

658
01:08:14.280 --> 01:08:15.720
Yeah.

659
01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:18.160
Joe Galloway. UPI.
How's it going. Colonel?

660
01:08:18.240 --> 01:08:21.640
We've been flat to the boards since last night.
and we're outnumbered.

661
01:08:22.960 --> 01:08:26.600
More enemy coming too.
I saw a chain of lights coming down the mountain.

662
01:08:26.680 --> 01:08:28.840
Is that so?
Yes. sir.

663
01:08:28.920 --> 01:08:31.200
Well. I can't guarantee
your safety.

664
01:08:31.320 --> 01:08:33.400
Yes. sir. I know.

665
01:08:33.480 --> 01:08:36.440
Where you from. son?
Refugio. Texas. sir.

666
01:08:36.520 --> 01:08:39.800
Well. that's the first thing I heard
all day that makes any sense.

667
01:08:39.880 --> 01:08:43.320
Captain. you see those lights coming
down the trails on the mountain?

668
01:08:43.400 --> 01:08:46.400
On it right now. sir.
You fry them sons of bitches.

669
01:08:46.480 --> 01:08:48.360
Whiskey-Six. this is Trojan-Three.
Fire mission.

670
01:08:48.440 --> 01:08:52.400
Tango Foxtrot:
4-niner-6-5-6-niner.

671
01:08:59.360 --> 01:09:02.040
All operations are suspended
for the evening.

672
01:09:02.120 --> 01:09:05.800
Morning operations will be
scheduled for 0530 hours.

673
01:09:36.760 --> 01:09:37.880
Where's Crandall?

674
01:09:37.920 --> 01:09:40.520
Where's Crandall?
He's right there. sir.

675
01:09:41.760 --> 01:09:44.040
You led my men into a hot LZ.

676
01:09:44.120 --> 01:09:45.800
Somebody had to fly out the wounded.

677
01:09:45.880 --> 01:09:48.760
Don't you play hotshot with me.
You know the rules.

678
01:09:48.840 --> 01:09:51.560
You suckered us in there.
Do it again. I'll have you busted!

679
01:09:51.600 --> 01:09:55.560
You got the balls to face me.
but not the balls to face the enemy?

680
01:09:56.640 --> 01:09:58.560
Get outta here.
Whoa!

681
01:09:58.640 --> 01:10:01.360
I ever see you again. I'll kill you.

682
01:10:05.160 --> 01:10:06.600
That's right.

683
01:10:15.320 --> 01:10:17.200
Quite a day. huh?

684
01:10:22.560 --> 01:10:24.520
Tomorrow will be worse.

685
01:10:27.400 --> 01:10:30.040
If they make it to tomorrow.

686
01:10:39.920 --> 01:10:42.840
Ernie. it's pitch black.
I can't see anything. but I can smell 'em.

687
01:10:43.960 --> 01:10:45.640
Dead bodies stink. Bungum.

688
01:10:45.680 --> 01:10:49.080
No. it's not the dead ones.
I can smell them crawling up on us.

689
01:10:50.160 --> 01:10:52.080
I'm telling you.

690
01:10:56.720 --> 01:11:00.840
I need illumination. 6-5-0. 1-5-0.

691
01:11:18.760 --> 01:11:21.440
I need artillery on previously established targets!

692
01:11:21.520 --> 01:11:24.840
Alpha. Bravo and Charlie! Fire for effect!

693
01:11:24.880 --> 01:11:26.840
Fire for effect!

694
01:11:29.320 --> 01:11:32.400
Save your ammo!
Cease fire!

695
01:11:33.480 --> 01:11:34.560
Is anybody hit?

696
01:11:36.600 --> 01:11:39.880
Captain. if you guys are coming
you gotta let us know.

697
01:11:39.920 --> 01:11:42.880
It's pitch black out here. I don't
wanna shoot any of our own guys.

698
01:11:44.960 --> 01:11:46.400
Savage...

699
01:11:47.640 --> 01:11:49.600
we can't make it tonight.

700
01:11:51.960 --> 01:11:55.000
Don't worry.
You're gonna make it.

701
01:11:55.800 --> 01:11:58.240
We'll come get you in the morning.

702
01:12:00.800 --> 01:12:02.480
Yes. sir.

703
01:12:03.800 --> 01:12:05.200
Out.

704
01:12:59.560 --> 01:13:01.720
You're doing a fine job. son.

705
01:13:01.760 --> 01:13:05.320
Don't worry. We gave them
more than they gave us today.

706
01:13:06.040 --> 01:13:07.960
How you boys doing?
Fine. sir.

707
01:13:08.040 --> 01:13:11.120
You keep doing what you're doing.
we'll be fine.

708
01:13:12.200 --> 01:13:16.080
Your men have done a hell of a job today.
Lieutenant Geoghegan.

709
01:13:16.160 --> 01:13:18.920
They won't get through us. sir.
You can count on it.

710
01:13:19.000 --> 01:13:20.680
I know that. Jack.

711
01:13:20.760 --> 01:13:22.160
Keep it up. son.

712
01:13:24.200 --> 01:13:26.480
It's Rear Headquarters. sir.

713
01:13:26.560 --> 01:13:27.880
How is it out there. Colonel?

714
01:13:27.920 --> 01:13:30.120
We're surrounded. but we're holding on. sir.

715
01:13:32.120 --> 01:13:35.200
Sir. I need a confirmed count
of our dead and wounded.

716
01:13:35.320 --> 01:13:37.840
I got to know where all my boys are.

717
01:13:37.880 --> 01:13:39.120
You'll get it. Hal.

718
01:13:43.240 --> 01:13:44.440
Here they come.

719
01:13:44.520 --> 01:13:45.720
Captain Edwards.

720
01:13:47.560 --> 01:13:48.880
We need illumination
on the perimeter.

721
01:13:48.960 --> 01:13:51.080
Whiskey-Five.
this is Hot Wire-Six-Alpha.

722
01:13:51.160 --> 01:13:53.840
We need illumination now.

723
01:14:29.800 --> 01:14:31.240
Kathy?

724
01:14:49.000 --> 01:14:50.040
A telegram.

725
01:14:50.840 --> 01:14:53.880
A cab delivers a telegram.

726
01:14:53.960 --> 01:14:57.080
"The Secretary of the Army...

727
01:14:58.880 --> 01:14:59.840
regrets..."

728
01:15:58.880 --> 01:16:00.160
Mrs. Moore?

729
01:16:00.240 --> 01:16:02.160
Colonel Moore's wife?

730
01:16:04.480 --> 01:16:05.600
Yes.

731
01:16:07.320 --> 01:16:09.760
I need help
finding an address.

732
01:16:11.080 --> 01:16:13.440
I'm looking for...
You jackass!

733
01:16:13.520 --> 01:16:17.920
Do you know what this is?
Do you know what you just did to me?

734
01:16:30.720 --> 01:16:32.800
I don't like this job. ma'am.

735
01:16:34.200 --> 01:16:36.120
I'm just trying to do it.

736
01:16:40.840 --> 01:16:41.760
Wait.

737
01:16:42.680 --> 01:16:44.120
Wait.

738
01:16:47.480 --> 01:16:49.320
I'll take it to her.

739
01:16:56.360 --> 01:16:59.680
And if there are any others.
just bring them to me.

740
01:17:11.040 --> 01:17:12.720
Julie.

741
01:17:12.800 --> 01:17:15.040
I just went by to see Catherine.

742
01:17:15.120 --> 01:17:16.560
Everybody knows.

743
01:17:17.760 --> 01:17:20.200
No chaplains or counselors?
Cab drivers?

744
01:17:20.320 --> 01:17:22.200
The Army wasn't ready.

745
01:17:25.040 --> 01:17:27.440
I'll go with you.

746
01:17:27.520 --> 01:17:29.440
Thanks.
Who's it for?

747
01:18:11.800 --> 01:18:13.720
I thought she would hate me.

748
01:18:15.200 --> 01:18:17.760
Your husband
didn't start the war.

749
01:18:17.840 --> 01:18:20.760
They all knew this could happen.
and so did we.

750
01:18:42.680 --> 01:18:44.600
I'll take care of this.

751
01:18:44.680 --> 01:18:46.600
I'll go with you.

752
01:18:49.560 --> 01:18:52.120
We'll do one at a time.
Okay?

753
01:18:53.360 --> 01:18:54.760
We won't look.

754
01:18:54.840 --> 01:18:56.240
Okay.

755
01:19:52.240 --> 01:19:54.040
Julie...

756
01:19:54.120 --> 01:19:57.040
do you think there'll be
more telegrams tomorrow?

757
01:20:00.560 --> 01:20:03.000
If there are.
come and get me.

758
01:20:23.000 --> 01:20:26.480
In the name of the Father.
the Son and the Holy Ghost. amen.

759
01:20:28.120 --> 01:20:31.560
Out of the depths
I cry unto Thee. O Lord.

760
01:20:31.600 --> 01:20:33.560
Lord. hear my voice.

761
01:20:34.640 --> 01:20:39.320
Let Thine ears be attentive
to the voice of my supplications.

762
01:20:39.360 --> 01:20:42.080
Thou. O Lord.
shall mark our inequities.

763
01:20:43.840 --> 01:20:45.760
Lord. who can abide them?

764
01:20:48.800 --> 01:20:50.720
With Thee there is mercy.

765
01:20:53.160 --> 01:20:55.760
Grant them eternal rest. O Lord...

766
01:20:55.840 --> 01:20:58.240
and may perpetual light
shine upon them.

767
01:20:59.600 --> 01:21:03.720
And through the mercy of God.
may they rest in peace. Amen.

768
01:21:03.800 --> 01:21:06.760
In the name of the Father.
the Son and the Holy Ghost.

769
01:21:13.400 --> 01:21:15.800
Do you got a death wish.
Galloway?

770
01:21:15.840 --> 01:21:17.920
No. sir.

771
01:21:18.000 --> 01:21:19.920
Well. then why are you here?

772
01:21:24.440 --> 01:21:26.760
'Cause I knew these dead boys
would be here. sir.

773
01:21:35.640 --> 01:21:37.760
Why aren't you a soldier?

774
01:21:37.880 --> 01:21:39.760
You got the guts for it.

775
01:21:39.800 --> 01:21:41.800
My daddy was a soldier.

776
01:21:41.880 --> 01:21:46.000
My granddaddy. two of my
great-granddaddies was soldiers.

777
01:21:46.080 --> 01:21:47.960
Hell. that's how I came to be.

778
01:21:48.760 --> 01:21:51.520
Each of them lost a leg
in the Civil War.

779
01:21:51.560 --> 01:21:54.160
My Great-granddaddy Galloway.
he lost his left...

780
01:21:54.200 --> 01:21:57.160
and my Great-granddaddy Reid
lost his right.

781
01:21:58.640 --> 01:22:01.600
They met in a shoe store
in Galveston.

782
01:22:01.640 --> 01:22:04.920
Every year after that. same date.
same store. they'd get together...

783
01:22:05.000 --> 01:22:07.920
and pick out a new pair of shoes
for the two of them.

784
01:22:08.000 --> 01:22:09.920
You are shittin' me.
No. sir.

785
01:22:10.000 --> 01:22:11.440
I swear to God.

786
01:22:12.960 --> 01:22:16.560
Anyway. one had a daughter.
one had a son... my grandparents.

787
01:22:16.640 --> 01:22:20.040
What do you suppose the odds of them
having the same shoe size was?

788
01:22:22.200 --> 01:22:25.640
I don't know. Colonel.
It was meant to be. I guess.

789
01:22:25.680 --> 01:22:27.120
Yeah.

790
01:22:28.400 --> 01:22:29.800
Meant to be.

791
01:22:31.600 --> 01:22:35.440
Sir. Galloways have been in every
war this country's ever fought.

792
01:22:35.520 --> 01:22:39.920
But when it came to this one.
I didn't think I could stop the war.

793
01:22:41.040 --> 01:22:43.840
I just thought maybe
I might try and understand one.

794
01:22:44.920 --> 01:22:48.040
Maybe help folks back home
understand.

795
01:22:50.680 --> 01:22:53.160
I just figure
I could do that better...

796
01:22:53.240 --> 01:22:55.920
shooting a camera
than I could shooting a rifle.

797
01:22:59.360 --> 01:23:00.760
Well...

798
01:23:03.000 --> 01:23:05.960
I sure hope you make it
through this one.

799
01:23:06.000 --> 01:23:07.480
You too. Colonel.

800
01:25:00.960 --> 01:25:02.880
Right 20!

801
01:25:19.400 --> 01:25:21.480
Put it right on 'em!

802
01:26:37.440 --> 01:26:38.880
Colonel. sir.

803
01:26:41.120 --> 01:26:43.480
Captain Nadal.
Sir.

804
01:26:48.640 --> 01:26:49.880
What is it. sir?

805
01:26:49.960 --> 01:26:52.040
Nothing's wrong.
except there's nothing wrong.

806
01:26:58.480 --> 01:27:01.720
Best get back to the termite mound.
You'll be fine. Go on.

807
01:27:01.760 --> 01:27:03.760
Roger that. sir.
Come on!

808
01:27:03.840 --> 01:27:06.000
All right. pass the word on.

809
01:27:06.080 --> 01:27:10.000
Every man fire three rounds
at anything that looks suspicious.

810
01:27:10.080 --> 01:27:11.520
On my signal.

811
01:27:34.160 --> 01:27:37.080
They're gonna hit us like this
along the whole perimeter.

812
01:27:37.160 --> 01:27:39.120
We gotta get back
to that termite mound.

813
01:27:39.160 --> 01:27:40.480
Better hang here. sir!

814
01:27:41.840 --> 01:27:43.320
Shit.

815
01:27:47.040 --> 01:27:48.720
We need a medic!

816
01:27:55.360 --> 01:27:57.120
Sir! Sir!

817
01:27:57.200 --> 01:27:59.480
Captain Edwards. Charlie Company.
on the ridge.

818
01:27:59.560 --> 01:28:01.000
Bob.

819
01:28:01.040 --> 01:28:02.640
They're inside the artillery!

820
01:28:02.720 --> 01:28:04.080
I need...

821
01:28:31.720 --> 01:28:33.440
I need a grenade!

822
01:28:45.560 --> 01:28:47.680
Go. Willie!
Come on. let's go!

823
01:28:53.360 --> 01:28:54.880
Godboldt down!

824
01:28:58.400 --> 01:28:59.560
I'll get him!

825
01:29:06.800 --> 01:29:08.200
Willie!

826
01:29:23.080 --> 01:29:24.480
Get those guys help!

827
01:29:24.560 --> 01:29:29.320
Captain Dillon. get Bravo Company
to send a platoon across the LZ...

828
01:29:29.400 --> 01:29:31.480
and support Charlie Company.

829
01:29:31.560 --> 01:29:34.120
Bravo-Six. this is Trojan-Three.

830
01:29:34.200 --> 01:29:37.400
And tell Charlie Company
to get real small in their holes.

831
01:29:37.480 --> 01:29:40.320
I'm gonna drop some artillery
right on top of'em!

832
01:29:40.400 --> 01:29:41.640
Charlie Company. get small.

833
01:29:41.720 --> 01:29:44.320
We got AT coming
right on top of your position.

834
01:29:44.400 --> 01:29:46.080
We're being overrun!

835
01:29:46.160 --> 01:29:48.800
Nah. boys!
We're gonna win this fight.

836
01:30:35.200 --> 01:30:39.360
Yes. sir. they brought a main force
of VC battalion against us too.

837
01:30:39.440 --> 01:30:42.400
Colonel. I request you dispatch
another company of reinforcements...

838
01:30:42.480 --> 01:30:46.480
for movement as soon as it can be
accomplished without undue risk.

839
01:30:46.560 --> 01:30:49.000
Done.
How bad is it. Hal?

840
01:30:53.960 --> 01:30:56.160
It's getting pretty sporty
down here. sir.

841
01:30:58.600 --> 01:31:00.680
Get out of the way!

842
01:31:10.120 --> 01:31:12.640
Medic!
Get a medic over here!

843
01:31:17.040 --> 01:31:20.400
What's your name. soldier?
Jimmy Nakayama.

844
01:31:20.480 --> 01:31:22.400
I got a baby being born today.

845
01:31:22.480 --> 01:31:24.680
Oh. wow! Congratulations!
Thanks!

846
01:31:29.360 --> 01:31:30.720
Medic!

847
01:31:30.800 --> 01:31:32.960
Medic!

848
01:31:35.800 --> 01:31:38.040
Can't take no pictures
lying down there. sonny.

849
01:31:41.400 --> 01:31:43.040
Down. right there.

850
01:31:47.920 --> 01:31:49.720
I'm a noncombatant. sir.

851
01:31:49.800 --> 01:31:51.840
Ain't no such thing today. boy.

852
01:31:56.600 --> 01:31:57.840
Shit.

853
01:31:59.920 --> 01:32:02.040
Why aren't those mortars firing?

854
01:32:02.080 --> 01:32:04.160
What's the problem here?

855
01:32:04.200 --> 01:32:05.680
These tubes are red hot. sir.

856
01:32:05.720 --> 01:32:08.480
I'm afraid we're gonna
cook a round off and blow us all up.

857
01:32:08.520 --> 01:32:11.480
We can't cool 'em off
'cause we're all out of water.

858
01:32:17.680 --> 01:32:19.760
Come on!
What are you waiting for?

859
01:32:19.800 --> 01:32:21.720
Jimmy. come on.

860
01:32:22.760 --> 01:32:24.640
Go. go. go.

861
01:32:24.680 --> 01:32:26.960
Yeah. one more.

862
01:32:48.640 --> 01:32:50.360
Gentlemen...

863
01:32:50.440 --> 01:32:52.480
prepare to defend yourselves.

864
01:33:02.760 --> 01:33:03.960
Grenade!

865
01:33:51.960 --> 01:33:54.600
Negative! Negative!
Stand by!

866
01:33:54.640 --> 01:33:58.800
My pilots do not see the enemy.
They cannot pick out our friendlies.

867
01:33:58.880 --> 01:34:00.520
Bravo-Six. say again.

868
01:34:00.600 --> 01:34:03.840
You gotta tell your company
commander to pop smoke now.

869
01:34:03.880 --> 01:34:07.240
They need to mark the lines now!
We have no lines!

870
01:34:07.320 --> 01:34:10.560
We have enemies and friendlies
mixed in all over the place.

871
01:34:10.640 --> 01:34:12.600
Sir. our perimeter is collapsing.

872
01:34:12.680 --> 01:34:14.920
Alpha Company and Bravo Company
cannot hold.

873
01:34:14.960 --> 01:34:16.920
Charlie Company is being overrun.

874
01:34:19.720 --> 01:34:21.840
Net call! Net call!

875
01:34:21.920 --> 01:34:23.840
Keep this net clear!

876
01:34:39.720 --> 01:34:41.160
Hastings!

877
01:34:45.320 --> 01:34:46.840
Broken arrow!

878
01:34:49.520 --> 01:34:51.680
Broken arrow!

879
01:34:51.760 --> 01:34:54.840
I say again!
Broken arrow!

880
01:34:54.920 --> 01:34:57.000
We have broken arrow!

881
01:34:57.080 --> 01:34:58.600
Confirm. Broken arrow.

882
01:34:58.640 --> 01:35:00.560
Broken arrow confirmed.

883
01:35:00.600 --> 01:35:01.760
Broken arrow?

884
01:35:01.800 --> 01:35:03.920
That means that an American unit
has been overrun.

885
01:35:03.960 --> 01:35:06.760
It calls in every combat aircraft
for support.

886
01:35:06.800 --> 01:35:09.920
My God. there's no hiding it now.

887
01:35:31.200 --> 01:35:33.920
Charlie Company. report!
Signal is out!

888
01:35:33.920 --> 01:35:36.120
Bravo Company. report!

889
01:35:36.200 --> 01:35:40.160
Roger that!
Planes are on their way. Colonel!

890
01:35:41.000 --> 01:35:42.120
Sir!

891
01:35:46.120 --> 01:35:47.600
Roger that!

892
01:35:58.680 --> 01:36:01.080
We have planes
at every 1.000 feet...

893
01:36:01.120 --> 01:36:04.160
from 7.000 to 35.000...
we'll get 'em. sir!

894
01:36:06.240 --> 01:36:09.640
Advancing north
on our position at 1 -5-0.

895
01:36:27.760 --> 01:36:30.000
Nine-six-two-five-zero-seven--

896
01:36:37.440 --> 01:36:40.320
They're getting closer in
on 3-1 -5 degrees!

897
01:36:40.360 --> 01:36:44.160
That's 0-5-0!
Repeat. 0-5-0!

898
01:36:50.360 --> 01:36:51.720
Goddamn it.

899
01:37:03.400 --> 01:37:07.480
Company sighted out in the open.
advancing north on our position.

900
01:37:07.560 --> 01:37:10.840
They're advancing on
3-1 -5 degrees at 1 -5-0.

901
01:37:12.480 --> 01:37:16.000
Bring it closer in
on 3-1 -5 degrees at 0-5-0...

902
01:37:16.080 --> 01:37:19.080
Charlie. call that
son of a bitch off!

903
01:37:19.120 --> 01:37:21.120
Call an abort now!

904
01:37:21.200 --> 01:37:22.120
Pull up!

905
01:37:24.440 --> 01:37:26.160
Get down!

906
01:37:53.240 --> 01:37:55.960
Charlie. listen to me.
You're keeping us alive now.

907
01:37:56.040 --> 01:37:58.960
You forget about that one
and you keep 'em coming in.

908
01:37:59.040 --> 01:38:00.640
You're doing well. son.

909
01:38:03.080 --> 01:38:05.080
Seven-oh-two...

910
01:38:05.120 --> 01:38:07.120
Attack against the tree line.

911
01:38:18.040 --> 01:38:20.720
Medic! Medic!

912
01:38:35.400 --> 01:38:38.520
Oh. God! Jimmy.
You know this guy?

913
01:38:38.560 --> 01:38:40.720
You know him? Talk to him.
Just talk to him!

914
01:38:41.560 --> 01:38:43.520
Jimmy. do you hear me?

915
01:38:43.600 --> 01:38:45.760
It's Joe.
It's Joe Galloway.

916
01:38:45.840 --> 01:38:49.160
Doc's giving you morphine.
We're gonna get you out of here.

917
01:38:55.800 --> 01:38:58.800
We gotta get him to
the landing zone. Grab his legs!

918
01:39:11.040 --> 01:39:13.880
You gotta get him out of here.
Hey! Hey!

919
01:39:13.920 --> 01:39:16.880
I can't help you!
You gotta do it by yourself!

920
01:39:16.960 --> 01:39:19.520
Get him on that chopper. okay?
Yes. sir.

921
01:40:18.480 --> 01:40:20.840
Tell my wife I love her...

922
01:40:20.920 --> 01:40:23.000
and my baby!

923
01:40:23.080 --> 01:40:25.560
You tell'em!

924
01:41:51.080 --> 01:41:52.680
Captain Nadal.
Sir...

925
01:41:52.760 --> 01:41:55.320
Now that we put 'em back on
their heels. we got us a lull.

926
01:41:55.400 --> 01:41:56.720
I want you to attack.

927
01:41:56.800 --> 01:41:59.560
I want you to go over there
and rescue that cut off platoon.

928
01:41:59.640 --> 01:42:02.720
Yes. sir!
First Squad. move out!

929
01:42:04.400 --> 01:42:06.640
Come on. guys.
Move it!

930
01:42:10.920 --> 01:42:12.200
Add fifty.

931
01:42:12.800 --> 01:42:14.800
Keep moving the artillery forward!

932
01:42:14.920 --> 01:42:17.240
Keep walking the artillery forward!

933
01:42:17.320 --> 01:42:18.400
Spread it out!

934
01:42:22.320 --> 01:42:24.440
Move it!

935
01:42:26.920 --> 01:42:29.680
Move it!
Keep moving forward!

936
01:42:45.600 --> 01:42:48.120
Sergeant Savage.
you guys still here?

937
01:43:06.560 --> 01:43:09.240
We have 40 KIA.
we have two MIA.

938
01:43:09.320 --> 01:43:11.240
These are the latest numbers.
Over.

939
01:43:41.040 --> 01:43:44.640
That's a nice day.
Sergeant Savage.

940
01:43:52.640 --> 01:43:55.680
Forty dead.
two unaccounted for. sir.

941
01:43:55.760 --> 01:43:57.600
Right.

942
01:43:58.480 --> 01:44:01.360
All right. boys.
let's get 'em up and get 'em out.

943
01:44:10.160 --> 01:44:13.080
Let's get 'em out of here
and get 'em on the chopper!

944
01:44:16.080 --> 01:44:18.760
Since most of the men
being loaded on the chopper...

945
01:44:18.840 --> 01:44:20.240
are from Charlie Company...

946
01:44:20.280 --> 01:44:21.800
I want you to take their place.

947
01:44:21.920 --> 01:44:25.600
I'll show you where. Follow me.
Yes. sir! Let's go!

948
01:45:23.400 --> 01:45:25.960
Captain. have your men dig
some firing steps.

949
01:45:26.040 --> 01:45:28.200
Throw some dirt on those bodies.
keep the smell down.

950
01:45:28.280 --> 01:45:30.160
Roger. Sergeant Major.

951
01:45:30.240 --> 01:45:34.360
Kind of makes you wish you'd
signed up for submarines. don't it?

952
01:45:34.440 --> 01:45:38.960
Brigade headquarters wants you out
on the first chopper at dawn.

953
01:45:39.040 --> 01:45:42.640
What idiot would keep ordering that
in the middle of a goddamn battle?

954
01:45:42.680 --> 01:45:45.680
Gen. Westmoreland wants a briefing.
Give me the horn.

955
01:45:46.480 --> 01:45:48.240
I am in a fight...

956
01:45:48.320 --> 01:45:51.240
and I object to this order
to return to Saigon.

957
01:45:51.320 --> 01:45:53.480
Now. I will not leave my men.

958
01:45:53.520 --> 01:45:55.520
Is that clear?
Out.

959
01:46:03.120 --> 01:46:05.040
There's two of my men
unaccounted for out there...

960
01:46:05.120 --> 01:46:07.040
and it's where
the worst of the fighting was...

961
01:46:07.120 --> 01:46:08.920
so they'll be out there someplace.

962
01:46:09.000 --> 01:46:11.760
Let's go out and get 'em.
I'm with you. sir.

963
01:46:11.800 --> 01:46:13.320
All right.

964
01:46:13.400 --> 01:46:14.920
Let's go.

965
01:48:07.960 --> 01:48:09.920
They...

966
01:48:10.000 --> 01:48:11.640
brought another...

967
01:48:11.720 --> 01:48:13.800
Oh. God.
Julie. it's yours.

968
01:49:01.920 --> 01:49:04.240
He died keeping my promise.

969
01:49:35.240 --> 01:49:37.200
Sir. they're ordering us all out.

970
01:49:37.280 --> 01:49:39.640
All of us.

971
01:49:39.680 --> 01:49:42.080
They're gonna march reinforcements in.

972
01:49:42.120 --> 01:49:44.600
They don't understand a damn thing. do they?

973
01:49:45.400 --> 01:49:46.960
Can't get out.

974
01:49:49.960 --> 01:49:52.360
He's waiting up there in a cave.
and that's what he wants.

975
01:49:52.440 --> 01:49:54.600
The minute he sees live soldiers
hopping on a helicopter...

976
01:49:54.680 --> 01:49:57.520
he'll be all over us
and then he'll get what he wants.

977
01:49:57.560 --> 01:49:59.840
He'll get his massacre.

978
01:50:08.440 --> 01:50:11.120
Requesting permission
to rejoin the lines. sir.

979
01:50:14.840 --> 01:50:16.560
All right. son.

980
01:50:20.640 --> 01:50:22.680
Garry Owen. sir.

981
01:50:45.280 --> 01:50:48.040
I wonder what was going through
Custer's mind when he realized...

982
01:50:48.120 --> 01:50:50.400
he'd led his men into a slaughter.

983
01:50:52.080 --> 01:50:54.800
Sir. Custer was a pussy.

984
01:50:56.800 --> 01:50:58.560
You ain't.

985
01:51:01.440 --> 01:51:03.080
Goddamn.

986
01:51:08.160 --> 01:51:09.600
Hell.

987
01:51:13.120 --> 01:51:15.280
Right now they're planning
their final attack...

988
01:51:15.360 --> 01:51:17.440
the one that will finish us off.

989
01:51:18.320 --> 01:51:20.760
They'll nibble at us all night.
then...

990
01:51:20.800 --> 01:51:23.840
come dawn they'll hit us
with everything they got.

991
01:51:25.400 --> 01:51:28.000
That's what I'd do if I was him.

992
01:51:33.040 --> 01:51:36.640
Sergeant Major. hand out
the last of the ammunition.

993
01:51:36.720 --> 01:51:38.640
Yes. sir.

994
01:52:59.440 --> 01:53:00.840
Fix bayonets.

995
01:57:18.360 --> 01:57:20.920
You were wondering
how Custer felt. sir.

996
01:57:22.520 --> 01:57:24.120
You ought to ask him.

997
01:59:42.720 --> 01:59:44.320
Sergeant Savage!

998
01:59:53.000 --> 01:59:55.280
Checking the dead enemies
for documents...

999
01:59:55.360 --> 01:59:57.920
and I found this on the guy
that tried to bayonet you.

1000
01:59:57.960 --> 02:00:00.560
Translated some of it.
mostly personal.

1001
02:00:00.640 --> 02:00:03.240
Thought you might wanna have
a look at it.

1002
02:00:34.920 --> 02:00:37.680
What was that?
It's American artillery.

1003
02:00:40.440 --> 02:00:42.240
Friendly fire.

1004
02:00:42.320 --> 02:00:44.240
How many casualties?

1005
02:00:46.480 --> 02:00:49.120
What the hell happened here. Joe?

1006
02:00:53.760 --> 02:00:55.360
Hey. Joe.

1007
02:00:57.120 --> 02:00:59.160
Colonel Moore!

1008
02:01:01.560 --> 02:01:03.800
Colonel!
Colonel Moore!

1009
02:01:06.840 --> 02:01:09.400
What is the key to your victory?
Sir. tell us how you feel.

1010
02:01:09.480 --> 02:01:11.640
Do you feel the States
will be forced...

1011
02:01:11.720 --> 02:01:13.680
to take the North Vietnamese
more seriously?

1012
02:01:13.680 --> 02:01:16.680
How do you feel about
the loss of your men. sir?

1013
02:01:16.760 --> 02:01:19.520
Have you notified
the families. sir?

1014
02:02:34.400 --> 02:02:36.320
I'm glad you made it. son.

1015
02:02:37.440 --> 02:02:39.760
Thank you. sir.
You too.

1016
02:02:44.640 --> 02:02:46.680
I'll never forgive myself.

1017
02:02:49.040 --> 02:02:50.800
For what. sir?

1018
02:02:55.800 --> 02:02:57.720
That my men...

1019
02:03:01.560 --> 02:03:04.040
That my men died and I didn't.

1020
02:03:26.320 --> 02:03:28.480
Sir. I don't...

1021
02:03:28.560 --> 02:03:31.200
I don't know how to tell this story.

1022
02:03:32.560 --> 02:03:34.840
Well. you got to. Joe.

1023
02:03:36.720 --> 02:03:39.600
You tell the American people
what these men did here.

1024
02:03:44.320 --> 02:03:46.560
You tell 'em how my troopers died.

1025
02:03:53.160 --> 02:03:54.760
Yes. sir.

1026
02:03:59.320 --> 02:04:00.920
Thank you.

1027
02:04:48.920 --> 02:04:51.960
All of our men. living and dead.
are off the field. sir.

1028
02:04:52.040 --> 02:04:53.960
Well done. Sergeant Major.

1029
02:06:51.160 --> 02:06:54.360
In Saigon. Hal Moore's superiors
congratulated him...

1030
02:06:54.440 --> 02:06:57.360
for killing over 1800
enemy soldiers.

1031
02:06:58.640 --> 02:07:01.040
Then ordered him to lead
the men of the 7th Cavalry...

1032
02:07:01.080 --> 02:07:03.520
back into the Valley of Death.

1033
02:07:03.600 --> 02:07:05.480
He led them...

1034
02:07:05.560 --> 02:07:07.680
and fought beside them...

1035
02:07:07.720 --> 02:07:10.360
for 235 more days.

1036
02:07:32.160 --> 02:07:35.080
Kids. go to bed.
Isn't there someone at the door?

1037
02:07:35.160 --> 02:07:37.360
Go to bed!

1038
02:08:17.560 --> 02:08:20.880
Children. your daddy's home!
Daddy!

1039
02:08:26.880 --> 02:08:29.800
Some had families waiting.

1040
02:08:29.880 --> 02:08:33.600
For others. their only family
would be the men they bled beside.

1041
02:08:33.680 --> 02:08:37.600
There were no bands. no flags...

1042
02:08:37.680 --> 02:08:40.240
no honor guards to welcome them home.

1043
02:08:41.520 --> 02:08:45.000
They went to war because
their country ordered them to.

1044
02:08:45.080 --> 02:08:48.080
But in the end they fought
not for their country or their flag.

1045
02:08:49.560 --> 02:08:51.840
They fought for each other...

1046
02:08:55.680 --> 02:08:57.400
Dear Barbara...

1047
02:08:57.480 --> 02:09:02.480
I have no words to express to you
my sadness of the loss of Jack.

1048
02:09:03.800 --> 02:09:06.320
The world is a lesser place
without him.

1049
02:09:07.400 --> 02:09:10.040
But I know he is with God
and the angels.

1050
02:09:10.120 --> 02:09:13.960
And even heaven is improved
by his presence there.

1051
02:09:15.440 --> 02:09:17.560
I know you. too.
are sure of this...

1052
02:09:17.640 --> 02:09:21.200
and yet this knowledge
can't diminish his loss...

1053
02:09:21.320 --> 02:09:23.160
and your grief.

1054
02:09:24.200 --> 02:09:27.520
With abiding respect and affection.
Hal Moore.

1055
02:09:40.640 --> 02:09:42.800
We who have seen war...

1056
02:09:42.880 --> 02:09:45.120
will never stop seeing it.

1057
02:09:47.800 --> 02:09:51.600
In the silence of the night.
we will always hear the screams.

1058
02:09:55.760 --> 02:09:58.000
So this is our story...

1059
02:09:59.520 --> 02:10:02.200
for we were soldiers once...

1060
02:10:02.320 --> 02:10:04.200
and young.

1061
02:10:42.720 --> 02:10:54.320
Subtitled *** by Kurgan ***

1062
02:10:54.720 --> 02:11:08.720
Subtitles LoS PiRaTaS 2002
